ally bad.\n现在看场电影至少要花上10英镑——真是太贵了。"], ['ADJ-GRADED\nYou can say that something is not bad to mean that it is quite good or acceptable, especially when you are rather surprised about this.', "（尤表示惊讶）不错的，不坏的，挺好的\n'How much is he paying you?' — 'Oh, five thousand.' —'Not bad.'...\n“他给你多少钱？”——“哦，5,000。”——“挺不错嘛。”\n'How are you, mate?' — 'Not bad, mate, how's yourself?'...\n“最近怎么样，老兄？”——“还不错，你呢？”"], ["ADJ-GRADED\nA bad person has morally unacceptable attitudes and behaviour.\nI was selling drugs, but I didn't think I was a bad person...\nHe does not think that his beliefs make him any worse than any other man.", '邪恶的；不道德的\n我贩卖毒品，但我并不觉得自己是个坏人。\n他觉得自己的信仰并不让他比其他人更邪恶。'], ['ADJ-GRADED\nA bad child disobeys rules and instructions or does not behave in a polite and correct way.\nYou are a bad boy for repeating what I told you...\nMany parents find it hard to discourage bad behaviour.', '不听话的；调皮的；捣蛋的\n重复我对你说的话，你真是个捣蛋鬼。\n很多父母觉得要孩子循规蹈矩是件很难的事情。'], ["ADJ-GRADED\nIf you are in a bad mood, you are angry and behave unpleasantly to people.\nShe is in a bit of a bad mood because she's just given up smoking.", '易怒的；乖戾的；阴郁的\n因为她刚刚戒烟，所以脾气有点大。'], ["ADJ-GRADED\nIf you feel bad about something, you feel rather sorry or guilty about it.\nYou don't have to feel bad about relaxing...\nI feel bad that he's doing most of the work...", '抱歉的；难过的；内疚的\n你不必为放松感到内疚。\n大部分工作都是他在干，我觉得很过意不去。'], ['ADJ\nIf you have a bad back, heart, leg, or eye, it is injured, diseased, or weak.\nAlastair has a bad back so we have a hard bed.', '受伤的；有病的；虚弱的\n阿拉斯泰尔背部有毛病，所以我们睡硬板床。'], ['ADJ\nFood that has gone bad is not suitable to eat because it has started to decay.\nThey bought so much beef that some went bad.', '变质的；腐烂的\n他们买了太多牛肉，有些都变质了。'], ["ADJ-GRADED\nBad language is language that contains offensive words such as swear words.\nI don't like to hear bad language in the street...\nI said a bad word.", '污秽的；咒骂的\n我不喜欢在街上听见一些污言秽语。\n我说了一句脏话。'], ['PHRASE\nIf you say that it is too bad that something is the case, you mean you are 